item.title: When and Why did you come to Mopar?
item.dc:creator: @Buzzy Buzzy
item.description:
@Buzzy wrote:

First cheat site I went to, was rstools.prv.pl, rest in peace. It was Friday’s site. He had links on there to other sites, that’s how I found Sythe and Kaitnieks.

I joined here on my first account on March 19th, 2006 under the name Fuez666. I had been visiting for a pretty long time before though.

I saw Mopar on Kait’s site a lot, and loved the things he did… I still remember what his signature was…

Money
O-I forget
Power
A-I forget
Respect

Then I heard he started a site, and went to it. Back when Mopar was known for something other than Moparscape, but an amazing scar scripter. I still remember staying on until 2 in the morning in the aryan section, trying to write scripts, and then I just stopped playing RuneScape and coming to Mopar all together after Aryan died.

Then, I came back in July of '06 under this name, and started going to the tut, and 3rd party programs. I remember posting torrent sites I found, or making random ass tuts that people laughed their asses off at, yet still found them funny.

Now, I don’t play RuneScape, and Mopar’s site has changed, a lot. To be perfectly honest, if I hadn’t come here back when this place was huge, I wouldn’t have stayed. I stay now because I’m just attached to this community.

Read full topic

item.title: When and Why did you come to Mopar?
item.dc:creator: @Algas Algas
item.description:
@Algas wrote:

When kaitnieks went down (when ever that was) someone ( I just dont remember who) messaged me on msn telling me that moparisthebest opened a new forums to continue where kaitnieks.com left. He told me that everything would be the same except mopar would be in charge. I came here

and

Here I am. Atm I am doing my compulsory military service and will be very inactive till july. Just would like to remind you all that you guys have a great forums where to chat and where to chill and I hope you all will keep it that way.

At the end I would like to thank mopar (again?) for creating this community and for keeping kaitnieks legacy alive… Or have mopar created a whole new cult/community/legacy? Well maybe some new guy will make a topic for that one (I still remember when I made a topic where I was asking about OSi, what it is and what is it for? :D).
